Properties.Name: ObjectId

Properties.Name: SelectionsSize

Methods.Name: IsValid
Methods.Description: Given a PlaintextBallotContest returns true if the state is representative of the expected values.  Note: because this class supports partial representations, undervotes are considered a valid state.

Properties.Name: ObjectId
Properties.Description: A unique Ballot ID that is relevant to the external system and must be unique within the dataset of the election.

Properties.Name: StyleId
Properties.Description: The Object Id of the ballot style in the election manifest.  This value is used to determine which contests to expect on the ballot, to fill in missing values, and to validate that the ballot is well-formed.

Properties.Name: ContestsSize
Properties.Description: The size of the Contests collection.

Properties.Name: SequenceOrder

Properties.Name: DescriptionHash
Properties.Description: The hash of the string representation of the Selection Description from the election manifest

Properties.Name: Ciphertext
